<font color="#FF0000">POEMS OF ROBERT H. DIRR JR.</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 21 14:25:33 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&quot;The Promise&quot;<br><br>
A poem by Robert H. Dirr Jr.<br><br>
When I was 9, Blackie got run over by a truck and his head was smashed and<br>
The SPCA man came and scooped hum off the street with a black shovel.<br>
I sat on the curb and started to cry my ass off but dad yelled at me and said<br>
&quot;Knock it off, son, don't you know big boys ain't supposed to cry?&quot;<br><br>
And when dad rotted away from cancer cells and was so fucked up by the<br>
Morphine that he didn't know who I was, he asked me if I was the guy<br>
He killed in Germany.  I said that no, I wasn't, and he answered by fading back<br>
Into his diehard sleep while I promised myself never to cry for anyone again.<br>

<p><code>-- Bongo-Bob@msn.com  (Robert H. Dirr Jr.) </code><p>


